  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The software tool developed by Stocker et al. (2019) has garnered notable attention, with 12 mentions recorded across various online platforms, indicating its relevance and potential impact within the community.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The software tool titled \"stineb/rpmodel,\" developed by Benjamin Stocker from ETH Zurich, represents a significant foundational research output within the fields of science, technology, engineering, and mathematics (STEM). This tool is currently hosted on Zenodo, a well-regarded repository for scientific data and software. Despite having no formal citations, the tool has attracted 12 online mentions, showcasing an emerging interest in its application and potential among peers and the broader community.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">The active mention of this software tool across various online platforms highlights its relevance beyond academic circles, signaling a growing public interest. While detailed community discussions on platforms like Wikipedia and Reddit are non-existent, the tool's visibility in other online contexts points to its practical implications and the possibility of fostering dialogue around its functionality and use cases.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">In terms of accessibility, the software tool has accumulated 52 views and 3 downloads as per the DataCite metrics, suggesting that users have engaged with the tool, reflecting its technical value and the potential for further reuse. The presence on Zenodo emphasizes a commitment to open access, allowing researchers to utilize it in their work freely, which is fundamental in fostering collaborative advancements in research.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">Currently, there is no documented funding for this software tool, but its development from a reputable institution, such as ETH Zurich, lends it credibility. The lack of an endorsed funding agency does not diminish the scholarly weight of the work but rather underscores a self-driven initiative by Stocker in contributing to the available tools in the scientific toolkit. Overall, while the tool is still in its early stages of dissemination, its evolving narrative is strengthened through community engagement signs and institutional backing.</p>",
